1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,833
Amazon Pinpoint Overview

2
00:00:03,500 --> 00:00:10,333
Amazon Pinpoint is an AWS service that
you can use to engage with your customers across multiple messaging channels.

3
00:00:11,458 --> 00:00:18,000
You can use Amazon Pinpoint to send email,
SMS text messages, voice messages, and push notifications.

4
00:00:19,458 --> 00:00:29,291
The Amazon Pinpoint Email API  provides
programmatic access to options that are unique to the email channel, and supplement the options provided by the Amazon Pinpoint API.

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,833
Features of Amazon Pinpoint

6
00:00:34,958 --> 00:00:36,666
Define audience segments

7
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:40,708
Reach the right audience for your messages
by defining audience segments.

8
00:00:42,958 --> 00:00:48,125
A segment designates which users receive
the messages that are sent from a campaign or journey.

9
00:00:49,958 --> 00:00:57,458
You can define dynamic segments based on
data that's reported by your application, such as operating system or mobile device type.

10
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,041
Messaging Campaigns

11
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:06,750
Engage your audience by creating a
messaging campaign.

12
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:13,500
A campaign sends tailored messages on a
schedule that you define.

13
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:22,000
You can create campaigns that send push
notifications, email, SMS text messages, and voice messages.

14
00:01:26,958 --> 00:01:28,791
Create User Journeys

15
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:35,041
Create custom, multi-step experiences for
your customers by designing and building journeys.

16
00:01:36,875 --> 00:01:42,791
With journeys, you can send messages to
your customers based on their attributes, behaviors, and activities.

17
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:51,166
When you build a journey, you design an
automated workflow of activities that perform a variety of different actions.

18
00:01:54,125 --> 00:01:55,875
Provide Consistent Messaging

19
00:01:57,541 --> 00:02:03,541
Design consistent messages, and reuse
content more effectively, by creating and using message templates.

20
00:02:06,208 --> 00:02:13,375
A message template contains content and
settings that you want to reuse in messages that you send for any of your Amazon Pinpoint projects.

21
00:02:16,958 --> 00:02:22,875
You can create templates for email, push
notifications, SMS messages, and voice messages.

22
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,125
Deliver personalized content

23
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,500
Send content that's customized for each
recipient of a message.

24
00:02:35,541 --> 00:02:43,000
Using message variables and attributes,
you can deliver dynamic, personalized content in messages that you send from campaigns and journeys.

25
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:54,666
With message templates, this content can
come from attributes that you create directly in Amazon Pinpoint, or from a machine learning model that you create in Amazon Personalize.

26
00:02:57,541 --> 00:02:59,250
Analyze User Behavior

27
00:03:00,541 --> 00:03:09,125
Gain insight into your audience and the
effectiveness of your campaigns and messaging activities by using the analytics that Amazon Pinpoint provides.

28
00:03:11,541 --> 00:03:17,375
You can view trends, in your users' level
of engagement, purchase activity, demographics, and more.

